# =============================================================================
# ATAK_DEPLOY_MANIFEST_URL — what goes here?
# =============================================================================
#
# This must be a full HTTPS (or HTTP) URL to a *small JSON file* that *you* host
# somewhere the PC running this installer can reach (your web server, VPS, object
# storage with public URL, etc.). It is NOT a mystery address: you choose the path
# when you upload the file.
#
# Example: you upload two files to your server:
#   https://maps.example.com/atak/manifest.json   ← put THIS url in the line below
#   https://maps.example.com/atak/atak-release.apk
#
# manifest.json content (minimal):
#
#   {
#     "atak_version": "4.10.1",
#     "atak_apk_url": "/atak/atak-release.apk"
#   }
#
# "atak_apk_url" can be a path like above (relative to the manifest URL) or a
# full URL. Optional: "plugin_apk_url" if you want the plugin downloaded from
# the server too; otherwise use ATAK_PLUGIN_REPO or ATAK_PLUGIN_APK below.
#
# Until you have a real host, you cannot fill this in—set up any static file host,
# drop the JSON + APK there, then paste the manifest’s URL on the line below
# (uncommented, no # at the start).
# =============================================================================

# Uncomment and replace with YOUR manifest URL:
# ATAK_DEPLOY_MANIFEST_URL=https://your-server.example/path/manifest.json

# Optional: your server endpoint to receive POST when installs finish (see script docstring).
# ATAK_DEPLOY_REPORT_URL=https://your-server.example/path/install-report
# ATAK_DEPLOY_API_TOKEN=

# Plugin (pick one; first match wins):
# ATAK_PLUGIN_APK=/path/to/plugin-debug.apk
# ATAK_PLUGIN_REPO=/path/to/your/plugin/android/project
# ATAK_PLUGIN_APK_URL=http://your-server.example/atak/plugin-release.apk
# ATAK_PLUGIN_GITHUB_REPO=atakmaps/BTECH-Relay   # latest GitHub Release .apk
# …or plugin_apk_url in manifest.json

# ATAK_PACKAGE_NAME=com.atakmap.app.civ
